main event: A radar object was observed at McClellan AFB for 10 minutes on June 16, 1961, but was not picked up by ground radar.
interesting points: The object disappeared over the horizon after being observed for 10 minutes., The object was identified as a radar anomaly but could not be explained., The sighting occurred at a scale of 5,000 yards., The object's course was noted at 0 degrees to 360 degrees., It was described that an unidentified object overshined the radar object before it vanished.
witness description: The report suggests multiple officers may have observed the object, but no specific witnesses are confirmed.
